<h1>Explain AI Privacy Policy</h1>

<small>Last Updated: July 18, 2026</small>

<p>
Explain AI ("we", "our", or "us") respects your privacy.
This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use the Explain AI mobile application.
</p>

<h2>Information We Collect</h2>

<ul>
<li>Name (if provided)</li>
<li>Email address</li>
<li>Authentication information through Google Sign-In or email/password</li>
<li>Study history</li>
<li>Flashcards</li>
<li>Quizzes</li>
<li>Study decks</li>
<li>Favorite content</li>
<li>Subscription status</li>
<li>AI prompts you choose to submit</li>
</ul>

<h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>

<ul>
<li>Provide AI-generated explanations</li>
<li>Create quizzes and flashcards</li>
<li>Save your learning progress</li>
<li>Synchronize your account across devices</li>
<li>Manage your subscription</li>
<li>Improve the app and fix bugs</li>
</ul>

<h2>Subscriptions</h2>

<p>
Subscriptions are processed securely through Google Play Billing.
Explain AI does not store your payment card information.
</p>

<h2>Authentication</h2>

<p>
You may sign in using Google Sign-In or an email/password account.
Authentication and account management are securely handled through Supabase.
</p>

<h2>Data Storage</h2>

<p>
Your account information and study data are securely stored using Supabase infrastructure.
</p>

<h2>AI Services</h2>

<p>
When you request an explanation or generate study content, the text you submit may be securely processed by our AI service providers to generate responses.
</p>

<h2>How We Protect Your Information</h2>

<p>
We use industry-standard security practices, encrypted communications (HTTPS), and trusted cloud providers to protect your information.
</p>

<h2>Your Rights</h2>

<p>
You may update or delete your account information within the app. If you need additional assistance, you may contact us using the email address below.
</p>

<h2>Children's Privacy</h2>

<p>
Explain AI is not intended for children under 13 without parental permission. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
</p>

<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>

<p>
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Updates will be posted on this page.
</p>

<h2>Contact</h2>

<p>
